Executors Framework in JAVA:
The Executors framework was introduced in Java 5 as part of the java.util.concurrent package
to simplify the development of concurrent applications by abstracting away many of the
complexities involved in creating and managing threads.

Before Exicutors Framework problems occurs:
1. Manual Thread Management
2. Resource Management
3. Scalability
4. Thread Reuse
5. Error Handling

3 core interfaces in Executors Framework:
i) Executor
ii) ExecutorService
iii) ScheduledExecutorService

